cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and Virtual Network Functions (VNFs) which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the placement and allocation of VNFs on servers in a network, which is related to distributed and cluster computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a model for Joint Placement and Allocation of Virtual Network Functions (JPA-VNF) which considers the balance between VNF investment with Quality of Services (QoS), which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a provable best-possible deterministic online algorithm based on dynamic programming (DP) and two additional randomized heuristics, which are related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes two randomized heuristics, the Las Vegas (LV) and Monte Carlo (MC) randomized algorithms, which are related to artificial intelligence.
